==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*skeran'', from Indo-European ''*(s)ker-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[skera]], Old Saxon [[sceran]] (Dutch [[scheren#Dutch|scheren]]), Old High German [[skeran]] (German [[scheren#German|scheren]]), Old Norse [[skera]] (Swedish [[skära]]).  The PIE root is also the source of Greek [[κείρειν]] ‘cut off’, Latin [[caro]] ‘flesh’, Lithuanian [[skìrti]] ‘separate’, Old Irish [[scaraim]] ‘separate’.

